content: Extremely Helpful for Studying

I was getting mid 90's on the practice test only to get a 50% on the real test. There was so many missing things and questions I never saw. The Written rewrites the questions and mixes them up its hardly the same at all. Prepware will only help you so much you need other study material. The FAA changed everything around JAN 2020 its all stupid now.
Do you have windows version? I want one for my laptop.
Very useful source to pest you're general writing test

This app does not work to give the test of FAA!
I have the hardware in my laptop, I feel that what is missing is the ability to highlight the correct answer. I hope the next update has this.

This app is great. Being able to study with the click of a button. Although, dont depend entirely on the app to pass. I passed with a 70% (by the skin on my teeth). The actual test is about having an understanding of these questions. I highly recommend getting the test prep Jeppesen books. Be sure to read the question, answer and explanation. Have a good understanding of what the meaning is they're trying to get across. Goodluck!

This app isn't as good as it should be for preparing you for the test. I used it in conjunction of the study guide book. I was scoring in the 80's consistently for almost a month and I failed with a 65%. When I took the test I was asked several questions that weren't in the study guide or in this app. I also noticed that some of the answers were completely changed. Some of the questions must be weighted more heavily. I got 43 out of 60 correct which is a 71.6% and not 65% when you do the math.
Nice and simple but it's missing 3 chapters and I'll mention it 1- nondestructive testing 2-hand tools and measuring devices 3- aircraft hardware
It was a good study tool to use. Learn each section then take a few practice tests, when good enough take the written test. I got 91 on written test
Great for studying
Greate app. I passed with an 85
Just failed my exam after getting a 96% on the practice tests. I have been studying for a month straight. The questions are not representative of the actual test.

I think the FAA doesn't give all the questions to prepware or something because there were questions that weren't on the preware material, there were also altered questions on the test but the app is easy to operate and gives you explanations for the problems.
Not what I'm looking for

Very good tool to study

NEED TO UPDATE! I had the FAA writens exam this week so i studied this app. Before studying i updated the app. I reviewed ALL QUESTIONS and when the testing happend, there were several questions not covered on this app that the FAA changed. I passed but it threw me off. Good app otherwise. Should be able to just hit "next" or "previous" on the test review instead of going back and forth to the questions

On some: ex: FAA-H-8083-30 reference, the answer is not "the starting point" it is "the intervention point". Per the 2013 test booklet. Please fix these, I have ben studying the wrong answer(s) for some time now and didn't know until now. Update/edit Dec 2019: Also, when studying sections, the app will close the section after some time away instead of allowing me to come back to the point i left off at. And the wrong answers issue still has not been addressed.
I passed the written exam using strictly this app.

Good start for preparation, app appears to be out dated, when i took the exam i have notice some questions that was not covered in the prep ware. It helps a bunch but to be safe, extend your research beyond the app aswell.

Excellent to help you get your general license. I got mine. The study and test are excellent. Statistics for scoring are a great help.Zero adds.

Just finish my General exam today, went to Baker's school in Nashville. My classmates still trying to finish their Airframe and today was the second day of school and I was able to finish Airframe the first day and General the second with no problem and all thanks to this Fu... apps. I've read a lot of bad reviews before take my test about this app that it wasn't helpful, but you know what? If you study all the questions. ALL!!! Not the test mode, the STUDY mode I assure you that you will pass. LISTEN, STUDY ALL THE QUESTION NOT JUST THE TEST MODE!!!!!! The test questions shuffle. I still recommend going to the school because they have some hands on classes that for those who don't have experience is very useful. Buddy. STUDY, STUDY, DO NOT F... AROUND.
I been using this app for the past 1 year and I finally finished my General Written exam with an 80%

The material is good, no complaints there. My gripe lies, and some will think this petty, but it could look much nicer. You pay $5.00 for an app you expect it to look good, not just work well. Why can't it be appealing like it's sister version used in the iPhone, especially since using it on an Apple device is cheaper? Also the references used on this app reflect the old FAA-H- 8083-30(Glencoe edition, I believe) not the most current version put out by ASA. The same goes for the computer download.

So far so good.  Installed it on my tablet and my phone.  Very portable, fast and reliable performance with no issues or force closes.  Has a study mode to practice every question on every chapter, and a test mode which throws 60 random questions at you.  You're not going to get a test analysis after testing that shows your weak areas, just a raw score showing what you missed.  A very basic bare bones study app but it has word for word all the questions the ASA Books have.  Well worth 5 bucks especially compared to other A&P prepware out there! But it does the exact same thing. Also, I purchased all three sections (Generals, Airframe, Powerplant) via iTunes for 9.99. On Android it will cost you $15. In any case regardless of platform, this is valuable study aid for passing the FAA written exams and helping you learn the material while in school. I'm only giving 4 stars due to the price differential between Android market and iTunes, and because the user interface is not as slick looking as the Ipod/Ipad.
